{"title_page": "TSV Hartberg", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = TSV Hartberg\n| image = TSV Hartberg.png\n| image_size = 250\n| fullname = Turn- und Sportverein Hartberg\n| nickname = \n| founded = {{Start date and years ago|df=yes|1946|04|29}}\n| ground = [[:de:Profertil Arena Hartberg|Profertil Arena Hartberg]]\n| capacity = 4,500\n| chairman = Brigitte Annerl\n| manager = [[Markus Schopp]]\n| current = \n| league = [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]]\n| season = [[2018\u201319 Austrian Football Bundesliga|2018\u201319]]\n| position = 11th\n| pattern_la1 = _whiteborder\n| pattern_b1 = _bluestripes4\n| pattern_ra1 = _whiteborder\n| leftarm1 = 0000FF\n| body1 = 0000FF\n| rightarm1 = 0000FF\n| shorts1 = 0000FF\n| socks1 = 0000FF\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2 = \n| pattern_ra2 = \n| leftarm2 = FFC000\n| body2 = FFC000\n| rightarm2 = FFC000\n| shorts2 = FFFFFF\n| socks2 = FFC000\n| website = https://www.tsv-hartberg-fussball.at\n}}\n'''TSV Hartberg''' is an [[Football in Austria|Austrian association football]] club based in [[Hartberg]], founded in 1946, which is currently playing in the [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Hartberg Performance Graph.png|280px|thumb|right|Historical chart of Hartberg league performance]]\nThe club was founded on 29 April 1946. They finished in 7th position in the 2007\u20132008 season while playing in the Third level [[Austrian Regionalliga|Regionalliga]]. On the last day of the 2008\u201309 season, TSV Hartberg finished in first position of the [[Austrian Regional League Central|Austrian Regionalliga East]] (third division). They won the eastern title and gained promotion to the 2009\u201310 [[Austrian Football First League|Second Division]]. In the 2010\u201311 season they finished at 10th and bottom position but survived by winning the relegation play-off, and in the 2014\u201315 season they were relegated to the third division for finishing at the same bottom position.\n\n==Stadium==\nStadion Hartberg is based in the Styria Hartberg district capital. It is a multipurpose sports facility, both for football matches and it is also suitable for athletics events. In addition, the stadium for other events such as music concerts. In 2006, the stadium of TSV Hartberg was expanded to that it could seat both home and away visitors with a capacity of 6,000 increasing from 4,500.<ref>http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/austria.shtml</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bundesliga.at/bewerbe/index.php?PHPSESSID=fe92ca2e378250b2e0a295d0e43e399e&sub1=2&sub2=2_4&sub3=2_4_1&vrnr=8142&PHPSESSID=fe92ca2e378250b2e0a295d0e43e399e |title=Archived copy |accessdate=9 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100918135106/http://bundesliga.at/bewerbe/index.php?PHPSESSID=aac4ffc89509bb2d7019a50f1f42172d&sub1=2&sub2=2_4&sub3=2_4_1&vrnr=8142&PHPSESSID=aac4ffc89509bb2d7019a50f1f42172d |archivedate=18 September 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Current squad==\n''Updated 3 November 2019.''\n\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1  |pos=GK |nat=AUT |name=[[Ren\u00e9 Swete]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=4  |pos=DF |nat=AUT |name=[[Michael Huber]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=6  |pos=DF |nat=AUT |name=[[Andreas Lienhart]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=7  |pos=DF |nat=AUT |name=[[Siegfried Rasswalder]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=8  |pos=MF |nat=AUT |name=[[Christoph Kr\u00f6pfl]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=9  |pos=FW |nat=SVN |name=[[Rajko Rep]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=10 |pos=MF |nat=AUT |name=[[Stefan Rakowitz]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=11 |pos=MF |nat=AUT |name=[[Lukas Gabbichler]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=14 |pos=DF |nat=AUT |name=[[Christian Klem]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=15 |pos=MF |nat=AUT |name=Marcel Schantl}}\n{{Fs player|no=16 |pos=MF |nat=AUT |name=Nino K\u00f6pf}}\n{{Fs player|no=18 |pos=MF |nat=AUT |name=[[David Cancola]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=19 |pos=FW |nat=CZE |name=[[Tom\u00e1\u0161 Ostr\u00e1k]]|other=on loan from [[1. FC K\u00f6ln]]}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|n